column7: BA_decile' groups Bay Area census tracts and Bay Area places into 10 groups (or deciles) each, for total population. For the access to transit indicator, values of 0 and 100 percent are prevalent, resulting in a vast number of equal values among the data. Equal values or 'ties' are assigned the mean decile rank. For example, in a database of 100 records where 70 records equal 0, 0 values span from the 1st to 7th deciles (70% of all data records). As a result, all 0 values will be assigned to the 4th decile: the mean between the 1st and 7th deciles.
